<table border=0 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=1>
	<tr>
		<td valign=middle align=left width=22><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=1 width=20 border=0></td>
		<td valign=middle align=right class="header">Profiles</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2"><hr size="1"></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text">Profiles allow content such as articles and pages to have their own profiles. Profiles will provide related information of the particular articles or pages.</td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text"><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=5 width=1 border=0></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="subheader">Adding A Section Profile</td></tr>
    <tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">1.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">
			Click on the New Profile button, fill up the following fields:<br>
			<li><b>Name</b> - Profile name</li>
			<li><b>Description</b> - Profile description</li>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">2.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the Save button to save the new profile. A New Field template will appear, see Adding Profile Fields below.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text"><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=5 width=1 border=0></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="subheader">Adding Profile Fields</td></tr>
    <tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">1.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">
			There are 8 types of fields available. The fields are explained below:<br>
			<li><b>Field Name</b> - Indicates the name or title of the field.</li>
			<li><b>Label</b> - Indicates the label/caption [e.g. Name, Email Address, Comments, etc.] under which the field name will be displayed when the user views the profile.</li>
			<li><b>Type</b> - Indicates the type of field (out of the 8 types).</li>
			<li><b>Options</b> - Represents a selection of all available values.</li>
			<i>Note: Only applicable to Select Box, List Box, Check Box, and Radio types.</i>
			<li><b>Default Value</b> - Indicates the default value for the field.</li>
			<li><b>Required Field</b> - Indicates whether the field in a compulsory field or not.</li>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">2.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">Once the required fields have been completed, click on the Update Fields button to save the new fields. Lastly, click on the Save Profile button to save the entire profile.</td>
	</tr>
</table>
